==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|epiphanie|lang=fro}} from {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|epiphania|lang=la}} from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ἐπιφάνεια||manifestation, striking appearance|tr=epiphaneia|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{term|ἐπιφαίνω||I appear, display|tr=epiphainō|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{term|ἐπί||upon|tr=epi|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} + {{term|φαίνω||I shine, appear|tr=phainō|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}. English [[Epiphany]] (of Christ) since the 14th century, generic use since the 17th century.

